\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid5059545\charrsid15550915 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10361243\charrsid15550915 I can't remember how the contact happened, but there was the kind of openness and interest in the B
BC in this kind of work. You see, there were people working for the BBC who had done similar work. They didn't call it oral history, but interviewing ordinary people. So it fitted very well with what they were doing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid10361243\charrsid15550915 Karen:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10361243\charrsid15550915 And the idea was to use the interviews already done?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid5059545\charrsid15550915 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10361243\charrsid15550915 Yes. And then subsequently, a number of other BBC people did use it ...
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid10361243\charrsid15550915 Karen:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10361243\charrsid15550915 How did they use it? They edited it?
