ally very awkward microphone, a big microphone, so in many ways, it's quite difficult to use. But it does produce beautiful quality recordings, and it's good for radio work, because you can cut up the tapes, it's an open reel, you see. So it does have som
e advantages. And, for a long time, it was thought to be the only kind of tape which had a long-term archival quality. It's only in the last ten years that cassettes have been regarded as okay for archives.
