\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid8224390 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10361243\charrsid15550915 The answer is that the only exception was the 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Coventry{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 set of interviews, where I wrote largely from the cut-up versions, rather than the, the l
ife story version. (We'll come to that.) But, for instance, in our most recent work, the one on stepfamilies, it's been terribly important to read the whole interviews right through. And I certainly think, as long as you have a manageable set, the number 
