e person relates to what happens with the others, it is all inter-connected, so you understand the family as a whole. And you also find repeating systems of people who do the same thing in each generation. Or reject. There are also rejections across gener
a
tions, so people do the opposite to their parents. And then the next generation does the opposite again, so they end up doing the same as the grandparents! So that was the idea. And we got some additional help from [Gill], we had some workshops with her w
here we looked at clinical interviews with families with transgenerational problems. 
