\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid15550915\charrsid15550915 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10361243\charrsid15550915 
Yes, I can read the whole transcript [of this interview] and think about that, and if there's things important that are missing, then we can talk about them. But, in terms of organisations, earlier on there's
 the Oral History Society, which is very important, and founding the journal, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\insrsid10361243\charrsid15550915 Oral History}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10361243\charrsid15550915 
. And there's the International Conferences which started in 1979, and I think it would be useful to record a little bit about that. And leading to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\insrsid10361243\charrsid15550915 
